#AD What’s the easiest way to connect with your child? 

Through play! There are several benefits to parent-child playtime, such as:

1️⃣ Develops important skills — gross motor, creativity, emotion regulation, group skills (just a few of many!)
2️⃣ Builds a strong relationship between parent and child
3️⃣ Benefits moms and dads health too!

That’s why this holiday season we decided to grow down, make memories and be kids again together! Fisher-Price was a huge part of my childhood, and I want to give my girls the opportunity to relive that childhood magic! 

We had an epic time playing with the @fisherprice Barbie® Little DreamHouse and Barbie® Convertible by Little People. Brought back a lot of nostalgia from the 90s! I can’t wait to continue building memories and using my creative imagination with my girls!

I’m going to keep it real with you…
Making this video was very hard for me because I had to look back at pictures and videos of the different stages of my #TSW journey and where it all began. But the reason I made the video, was to remind myself of all the good that happened despite the condition I was in. 

If you saw my reel, you wouldn’t know I was struggling with my health throughout the entire year. You wouldn’t be able see the pain, the tears, the frustration and anguish. 

This proves that you don’t really know what someone is going through no matter what they share on social media. You only see a glimpse of it - if anything. 
So be kind to yourself and to others 🫶🏼 

I wish you all a new year filled with happiness, health, success and prosperity!

Reflecting on our past year of marriage 💘

Allahumma barik. Please say a little prayer for us and our marriage. 

We usually plan a fun date night in/out depending on our mood. This year we went out for dinner and ended the night with a steaming cup of Kashmiri chai. 

Since the new year and our anniversary are one day apart, we like to reflect on our relationship at the end of every year. Here’s some of the reflection questions we asked each other that you can try with your partner!

✨When did you feel the most/least connected with me this year?
✨What do you wish we had done more/less of this past year?
✨How did we grow together this year?
✨How do you feel I best supported you this year? 
✨Were there areas where I could have better supported you this year?
✨Where do you think you could show up as a better partner? (and vice versa)
✨What were some of the biggest challenges we overcame as a couple this year?
✨What are your favorite activities for us to do together?
✨What would you like to see us accomplish together next year?
✨What did you learn about me this year?
✨What is your favorite “you and me” tradition or ritual?
✨What routines/habits would you like to see us implement this next year?
✨What areas of our relationship need the most improvement?
✨What is one thing that stands out to you that I did that really says “I love you” without saying “I love you”?

Join me on my decluttering journey!

Over the last few years, I’ve accumulated a lot of stuff from clothing to makeup, shoes and accessories. This past year I haven’t been able to use any of it because of my health condition. It just made me realize how most of the stuff I have is unnecessarily taking up space in my closet. The clutter was making me anxious, so I decided it’s time to do a major declutter/reorganization.

Setting the tone for the week ahead 🫶🏼

Sunday’s are usually very chill and usually spent at home, so I like to reset by cleaning three main areas: bedroom, kitchen/dining, and living room. I don’t do a deep clean. I just do a quick tidy up. Wash dishes, wipe countertops, change bedsheets, sweep/vaccum, and pick up and toys/objects off the floor. I’ll also plan for the week ahead in terms of cooking/cleaning so I can stay organized and on top of things — or try to be at least 😅

Ramadan Mubarak 🌙✨

As my girls get older, I want to incorporate new traditions for them during Ramadan to get them involved and excited for this holy month. My girls loved making + delivering the Ramadan jars to loved ones. It was a super fun family activity 🫶🏼

Ramadan Jars 🌙✨
Filled with pistachios, homemade chocolate covered dates and mini chocolate bars. 

✨Biscoff dates: Pitted and filled with lotus biscoff spread, dipped, and sprinkled with lotus biscoff cookies 
✨Snickers dates: Pitted and filled with peanut butter, dipped, and sprinkled with crushed peanuts. 
🍫The dates were dipped in melted milk chocolate after being filled. 

✨The jars were from @dollartree. We used tape to secure the lid and then used liquid glue to glue on the burlap ribbon around the edges (you can also use a hot glue gun). 

✨Ramadan tags were parcel tags from @dollaramafindsca.

To my fellow Muslim mommies:
❣️If you want to go all out and decorate, go for it. 
❣️If you choose to keep the decor to a minimum, that’s okay too. 
❣️If you want to surprise your kids with gift baskets, do it! 
❣️If you choose to connect with them in other ways, that’s okay too. 
❣️If you want to meal prep and have freezer meals ready in advance, go for it. 
❣️If you want to take it day by day, wing it or even order meal service, that’s completely okay too! 
❣️The important part is to set the right intention. 
❣️Motherhood = ibadah. The work you do around your house and with your children — whether it’s dressing them, feeding them, reading to them, playing with them, teaching them new things, or comforting them. 
❣️Do this with the intention of pleasing Allah, and your ibadah will count as worship. 
❣️Who said moms need to miss out on the blessings of this holy month?

Here’s how👇🏼 SAVE this 📌 

✨You can easily do this alone, with your spouse, a friend or even as a family. 

✨Break the page down into 3 categories. 
For this Dunya (the world) 
For the Akhirah (the hereafter) 
For others: parents, children, spouse, other family members, friends, anyone you personally know who’s suffering, those suffering around the world, etc. 

✨Recite this dua list after every salah, and more importantly at the time of breaking fast. 

✨Abu Hurayrah said: The Messenger of Allaah (peace and blessings of Allaah be upon him) said: “There are three whose du’aa’ is not rejected: a just ruler, the fasting person when [until] he breaks his fast, and the prayer of the oppressed person. It rises above the clouds and the gates of heaven are opened for it, and the Lord, may He be glorified, says, ‘By My Glory I will answer you even if it is after a while.’” (Narrated by al-Tirmidhi, 2525; classed as saheeh by al-Albaani in Saheeh al-Tirmidhi, 2050.) ”

✨When you’re making these duas; make them with full conviction in your heart that Allah hears you and will accept these duas.

📌 SAVE this freezer friendly recipe 

✨Ingredients:
2 medium ripe bananas 
2 eggs
1/2 cup milk of your choice 
½ teaspoon vanilla extract
1 ½ cups rolled oats
2 teaspoons baking powder
½ teaspoon ground cinnamon
¼ teaspoon salt
Olive oil or butter for frying

✨Add all ingredients to blender and blend for 30 seconds - 1 minute or until you get a smooth consistency. Recipe called for rolled oats. I only had steel cut oats but I would def recommend sticking to rolled oats for better texture. 
✨Lightly coat a griddle/pan with olive oil or butter and place over medium-low heat. Once pan is hot, use a spoon, ice cream scoop or a batter dispenser to add your batter to the pan. Make them as little or big as you want. 
✨Wait until pancake bubbles and then flip. Both sides should be a golden brown. 
✨Serve with your choice of syrup and top with any ingredients — bananas, chocolate chips, etc.

📌 SAVE these tips for your toddlers first movie🍿 

1. Make sure you choose the right movie. Obviously kid friendly 😜 Maybe something with their favourite character or something they already enjoy watching at home!

2. Skip the ads and trailers! Movies are long as it is and for a first time experience, kids might struggle to sit still for long. Try not to arrive too early, like when the ads and trailers are playing. 

3. Plan it right! Let them know in advance what to expect at the theatres, what the atmosphere is like (dark room, loud noises), what snacks to buy, and what’s expected from them (can’t walk around, limited talking, etc). 

4. Plan around their routine! If your kiddos still take naps, try to either go for an earlier movie so they can nap afterwards, or a later movie so they can be refreshed from their nap. 

5. Go with the flowww! If your little one can’t finish off the movie, it’s okay to leave! Or try to take a short break during the movie…either a pee break or to just hang out in the lobby and walk it off before going back in. 

And don’t forget to have fun! 🥰
